\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Softer 2020
\f0\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 \'93Softer freight volumes combined with lower rates could well be generating a reassessment of 2020 investment plans,\'94 Maly said.\cb1 \
\cb2 Trailer production continues to set monthly records. June is on track to be the sixth-best month in history. The five other monthly records have occurred since August 2018. About 160,000 trailers are queued for assembly, 6,000 units more than this time in 2018.\'a0\cb1 \
\cb2 With so few new orders and strong cancellations of existing bookings, both Ake and Maly expect production to slow in the fourth quarter and extend into 2020.\cb1 \
