\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Flatbed woes
\f0\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 Orders of dry vans and refrigerated trailers that carry mostly consumer goods are likely to hold up through the current quarter. Projections call for lower second-half orders of flatbeds used to haul building materials and other oversized objects for housing and construction.\cb1 \
\cb2 \'93There is a noticeable dropoff,\'94 Ake said. The reasons include overstocked dealers, a softening manufacturing sector, slower housing growth and moderating oil production.\'a0\cb1 \
\cb2 Flatbeds are a leading indicator of trucking industry health. Orders typically precede bookings for the trucks that haul them. Companies keep flatbeds in service longer to wait out uncertain times. That creates pent-up demand, which drives a peak-and-valley purchase cycle.\cb1 \
